m_q.target_metric: Three beaches with highest pollution levels (Indicator Level) in 2015 for the city with lowest summer (June, July, August) rainfall in 2015
filters: Focus on city with minimum summer precipitation
sub_questions: Which city had the least rainfall in summer 2015?
What are the pollution levels (Indicator Level) for beaches in that city in 2015?
Which three beaches have the highest pollution levels?

schema_conflicts: Precipitation files have city names in filenames but not in data columns
Community names in water-body-testing-2015.csv need to match precipitation city names
Year columns have different types: float64 in precipitation files vs int64 in water testing

scale_issues: Missing values in precipitation data (empty cells)
Multiple samples per beach may need aggregation
Different number of precipitation measurements per city
cross_source_conflicts: Precipitation data covers multiple years but only 2015 needed
Water testing has multiple samples per beach per year - need aggregation method

format_notes: Precipitation files have empty cells for missing data
Year values are floats but represent integers
Sample Date in water testing is datetime string
Multiple precipitation files for different cities

constraints: Summer defined as June, July, August
Beaches must be in the identified city
derived_filters: Sum Jun, Jul, Aug precipitation for each city
Filter water testing to Year = 2015 and matching Community
Aggregate beach pollution levels (max or average Indicator Level)
statistical_tests: Identify city with minimum summer precipitation
output_format_requirements: Should identify the city with least rainfall
